## Conditional Fetch

\"If it's a weekday, fetch my work calendar; otherwise, fetch my personal calendar. Then return the next event title.\"

Two branches, two fetches, one extraction. Still one form:

```scheme
(calendar/next-event-title
 (if (member (clock/day-of-week) '(monday tuesday wednesday thursday friday))
     \"work\"
     \"personal\"))
```

*[needs: calendar/next-event-title, clock/day-of-week]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire clock/day-of-week and calendar/* -->

The `if` expression closes the calendar-selection. The outer call closes the title extraction. No variable holding the calendar name. No variable holding the calendar object. One shot.

