## Nested Conditionals

\"If I have a meeting in the next hour and it's not already snoozed, show me a reminder. Otherwise, say nothing.\"

That's a guard inside a guard, with a fetch and a format. One form:

```scheme
(if (and (calendar/has-event-within? 60)
         (not (reminder/is-snoozed? \"next-meeting\")))
    (string-append \"Reminder: \" (calendar/next-event-title \"primary\") \" in less than an hour.\")
    \"\")
```

*[needs: calendar/has-event-within?, reminder/is-snoozed?, calendar/next-event-title]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire calendar/* and reminder/* -->

The `and` closes the two conditions. The `string-append` closes inside the `if`. The entire question-and-answer is one expression.

