## String Composition with Logic

\"Greet me by name if I've set one; otherwise, use 'Friend'. Then append the current hour in 12-hour format.\"

```scheme
(string-append \"Hello, \"
               (if (profile/has-name?)
                   (profile/name)
                   \"Friend\")
               \"! It's \"
               (number->string (let ((h (clock/hour)))
                                 (if (> h 12) (- h 12) (if (= h 0) 12 h))))
               \" o'clock.\")
```

*[needs: profile/has-name?, profile/name, clock/hour]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire profile/* and clock/hour -->

The greeting logic nests inside the string builder. The hour conversion nests inside a `let` inside a `number->string` inside the same string builder. One form, start to finish.

