## Nested String Matching

\"Check if the subject line of my most recent email contains the word 'invoice' (case-insensitive).\"

```scheme
(string-contains-ci? (email/subject (car (email/recent 1)))
                     \"invoice\")
```

*[needs: email/recent, email/subject]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire email/* to IMAP or a local maildir -->

The email fetch closes the subject extraction closes the string search. One form. (We assume `string-contains-ci?` is in the core library, or we define it inline if needed.)

Actually, let's define it inline so the example runs standalone:

```scheme
(let ((string-contains-ci? (lambda (haystack needle)
                             (let ((h (string-downcase haystack))
                                   (n (string-downcase needle)))
                               (string-contains? h n)))))
  (string-contains-ci? (email/subject (car (email/recent 1)))
                       \"invoice\"))
```

*[needs: email/recent, email/subject]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire email/* -->

Now the helper is local to the form. The entire question is still one expression.

