## Boolean Aggregation

\"Tell me if all of my houseplants were watered in the last 3 days.\"

```scheme
(every (lambda (plant) (<= (- (clock/unix-time) (plant/last-watered plant)) 259200))
       (home/plants))
```

*[needs: plant/last-watered, home/plants, clock/unix-time]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire plant/* and home/* to a local log or sensor data -->

We assume `every` is in the core, or define it inline:

```scheme
(let ((every (lambda (pred lst)
               (if (null? lst)
                   #t
                   (and (pred (car lst))
                        (every pred (cdr lst)))))))
  (every (lambda (plant) (<= (- (clock/unix-time) (plant/last-watered plant)) 259200))
         (home/plants)))
```

*[needs: plant/last-watered, home/plants, clock/unix-time]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire plant/* and home/* -->

Recursive `every`, lambda predicate, time subtraction, plant list—all one form.

