## Conditional Formatting

\"If my next calendar event is within 15 minutes, format it as '⚠️ SOON: <title>'; otherwise, just the title.\"

```scheme
(let ((minutes-until (calendar/minutes-until-next \"primary\")))
  (if (<= minutes-until 15)
      (string-append \"⚠️ SOON: \" (calendar/next-event-title \"primary\"))
      (calendar/next-event-title \"primary\")))
```

*[needs: calendar/minutes-until-next, calendar/next-event-title]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire calendar/* -->

We use a `let` to avoid fetching `minutes-until` twice, but the entire form—binding, conditional, formatting—is still one expression.

