## Multi-Step Transformation

\"Take the first 5 items from my reading list, extract their titles, join them with ' · ', and prepend 'Up next: '.\"

```scheme
(string-append \"Up next: \"
               (string-join (map article/title (list-head (reading/list) 5))
                            \" · \"))
```

*[needs: reading/list, article/title]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire reading/* and article/* -->

We assume `string-join` and `list-head` are in the core, or define them inline:

```scheme
(let ((list-head (lambda (lst n)
                   (if (or (null? lst) (= n 0))
                       '()
                       (cons (car lst) (list-head (cdr lst) (- n 1))))))
      (string-join (lambda (lst sep)
                     (if (null? lst)
                         \"\"
                         (if (null? (cdr lst))
                             (car lst)
                             (string-append (car lst) sep (string-join (cdr lst) sep)))))))
  (string-append \"Up next: \"
                 (string-join (map article/title (list-head (reading/list) 5))
                              \" · \")))
```

*[needs: reading/list, article/title]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire reading/* and article/* -->

Two helper definitions, a map, a slice, a join, a prepend. All one `let` form.

