## Substring Extraction

\"Extract the domain from my primary email address.\"

```scheme
(let ((email (profile/email)))
  (substring email (+ (string-index email #\\@) 1) (string-length email)))
```

*[needs: profile/email]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire profile/email -->

We assume `string-index` finds the position of a character. Lookup, search, slice. One `let` form.

Define `string-index` inline for standalone execution:

```scheme
(let ((string-index (lambda (s c)
                      (let loop ((i 0))
                        (cond
                          ((= i (string-length s)) #f)
                          ((char=? (string-ref s i) c) i)
                          (else (loop (+ i 1)))))))
      (email (profile/email)))
  (substring email (+ (string-index email #\\@) 1) (string-length email)))
```

*[needs: profile/email]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire profile/email -->

Helper, lookup, arithmetic, substring. One `let` form.

